The paper deals with the sample complexity of semi-supervised learning, which is a topic in machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of mixture models and the Wasserstein distance, which are common tools in the fields of statistics and probability theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
